Expand for example instructions ```console git remote add upstream https://github.com/TokTok/c-toxcore.git git fetch upstream pull//head git merge --ff-only FETCH_HEAD git push ```
**NOTE**: As work continues on the original Pull Request, this process will re-run and update (force-push) this Pull Request with updated style fixes as necessary. If the style is fixed manually at any point (i.e. this process finds no fixes to make), this Pull Request will be closed automatically. Sorry if this was unexpected. commit.message:
Refactor peer syncing

We now send each peer in a single packet instead of the entire
peer list in one big packet. This removes a theoretical hard
limit on the number of peers that can join a group and ensures
that the maximum packet size doesn't exceed the MTU of common
network media.

Some unnecessary syncing logic was removed. This will increase
the aggressiveness of syncing with more redundancy, but should
improve overall syncing speed.

Additionally, the ping packet now contains a checksum of the
public key hash of all confirmed peers instead of just the peer
count. This will ensure that sync requests will be made in
the case that all group peers have the same peer count, but a
different set of peers (i.e. group splits).

Finally - an unused 32-bit uint was removed from the sync request
packet.

commit.message:
Reduce unnecessary amount of group announcement spam

Instead of every peer refreshing their announcements every n minutes we ask
each peer to play a lottery every n minutes where their chance of winning
is relative to the number of peers in the group, and announce only if they
win. We only need a bare minimum of one announcement in the DHT at any given
time, so this ensures that while not constantly burdening the DHT with
unnecessary traffic.

commit.message:
Simplify and improve group handshake protocol

- We no longer have the peer who receives a sync request send the requestor's
  info to the rest of the group as this was redundant (and broken)

- Lots of unnecessary/duplicate code pertaining to handshaking was removed

- Message ID's are set to a fixed number when we send/receive handshake
  packets instead of incrementing. This is because it's impossible to
  proceed with the connection if either of those first two packets
  are lost, so incrementing the counters just messes up the order

- Sync responses no longer contain the number of peers being sent
  in the series of peer announces as this was unnecessary
